==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hyparterial
<hw>Hy`par*te"ri*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hypo-</ets> + <ets>arterial</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Situated below an artery; applied esp. to the branches of the
bronchi given off below the point where the pulmonary artery crosses the
bronchus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hypaspist</ent>⟦br⟧
